<Author>Lutzi1
<Content>Very convenient and comfortable with great beds! We stayed here after arriving on a late flight, and the experience was just so easy and convenient. To catch the free shuttle tot he hotel you just go to the bank of courtesy phones to the right of the main exit, and they will tell you when the next one is due (they are frequent). Then go out of the main exit, turn right and walk a few yards to the shuttle bus stop outside the easyjet office. All the staff I dealt with were all pleasant , helpful and polite. There was a minor hiccup with our rooms when we got there - no sofa bed for our daughter in our room - but that was very quickly and calmly sorted out with no fuss. We had a executive room with a sofa in and they are a good size and very comfortable. The bed was also extremely comfortable, so beware of that velcro pyjama feeling if you have a flight to catch the next morning ! The breakfast buffet is excellent with a really good choice and the service was extremely good. We were then taken again by free shuttle to the station. A really positive experience and a good start to our holiday. 
