<Author>jmcglynn
<Content>Great for the airport... We stayed here for a short weekend break in Berlin and it's a great hotel.The hotel is pretty much in the middle of nowhere so I wouldn't recommend staying there if you wanted to be close to the city centre. It took us about 40mins on the metro to get into Berlin. For the airport it's great, there's a shuttle every 20mins or so that will take you between the two and also stops off at the metro station.It cost us 拢35 for a double room (without breakfast which cost about 拢8 - there are some places, but not many, at the metro station if you don't want to pay that. Also some places at the airport) which was really good value considering the hotel looked pretty new. My husband said the gym was good and you can even do curling if you fancy it!!The food in the restaurant is fairly expensive, even the bar food would cost you about 拢6 for a salad! We ate in the bar area in the evening and the food was nice. It's also a nice little area to sit and chill in, although a bit drafty!!The staff were great, even changing our feather pillows to hypoallergenic ones due to allergies.Remember you will be on the East Side of Berlin - we didn't realise this at first and got into all kinds of trouble with the metro and underground system!! The metro stations are not great, further out there's no information on when the next one will arrive and you need to look at the front of the train to see where it's going. Further into the city centre the stations get a bit more technologically advanced!All in all, I would recommend this hotel. 
