<Content>Great Between Flights! Stayed here after arriving on a late flight. I couldn't be bothered to head into central Berlin, so had booked this Holiday Inn in advance. I hold a Platinum Card for Holiday Inn Hotels so was immediately upgraded to the best business room they had (having paid the princely sum of 50 Euro - now that's value!). The receptionist was welcoming and promised that a bottle of wine (complimentary) would be sent up to the room. The wine never arrived, but a plate of fruit and cakes did. Still, it was 11pm and I really wasn't in the mood for wine anyway! The room was over-average size for Europe, with a king-size bed, sofa, writing desk and tea/coffee making facilities and minibar. The bathroom was spotless (believe me, I check...if there's one thing I hate it's signs of other peoples' bathroom use....).Holiday Inn provides a shuttle bus from Sch枚nefeld Airport terminal as well as the S-Bahn station in Sch枚nefeld (which is basically in the same area). I took a taxi from the airport to the hotel, because it had been a long day and I weas basically to lazy to wait/contact the hotel. It cost 12 Euro. The bus runs twice an hour if I remember correctly, so no long waits here. The S-Bahn will get you into central Berlin in about 45 minutes - you may have to change trains, depending on which area of the centre you want to go to.All in all, this was a great choice after a late arrival. It was clean, comfprtable and welcoming and aircraft noise was insignificant (I think the airport is closed at night). One slight minus; the public areas are very smoker. As an ex-smoker I tend to find this a bit of a turn off. But that's more to do with German laws and regulations than the hotel itself. 
