<Author>MrsRaymondo
<Content>Great Hotel - handy to aiport We stayed here for 2 nights at the end of October - on arrival in Berlin and again on our last night. The hotel is situated close to the airport and the airport train station. The hotel operates a 24 hour free minibus between the hotel, the airport and the train station (queue at the 'Holiday Inn' bus stops outside). The bus circles every 20 mins between 8.00am and 10.00pm. Outside these hours you need to ring the hotel (the number is on the bus stops). The hotel itself is excellent - very clean and the rooms are spacious. Our first room had an iron/board and bath with shower. Our second room had a shower only with no iron. Both our rooms had tea/coffee making facilities and mini bar. On both occasions chocolates were left on our pillows. The staff were very friendly and helpful. Breakfast was not included in our rate but we paid separately for this (15.50 euro each). Although not cheap, the breakfast was excellent and set us up for the day (fruit, juices, yoghurts,cheeses, cereals, cold meats, various breads, toast, cooked bacon, eggs, mushrooms). Although quite a way out from the centre of Berlin, the hotel is excellent and a good choice if you have an early or late flight. But as the trains operate so regularly this is also a good and unexpensive base for sightseeing. Berlin transport offer a 'Welcome Card' for around 20 euro (depending on length of stay and area covered) which allows travel on trains/buses and underground for 2 or 3 days. If staying in the Holiday Inn Schoenefeld you will need the Welcome Card which covers zones A,B and C as the Holiday Inn is in zone C. 
