<Content>Great Holiday Inn As others have said, this is a great hotel if you are arriving at or departing from Berlin Schoenefeld Airport. It was a great start to our holiday, which took us to Poland and Estonia, and a good finish too, i.e. one night in the Holiday Inn at the beginning and end of our trip. The staff were all very friendly, the rooms a delight, with everything you could want for an overnight stay: hairdryer; coffee maker; mini bar; TV; even tissues in the bathroom, which was very well planned. We liked this hotel a lot, particularly as we got a very good rate, 45 euros a night, though breakfast was an extra 15 euros each per day. The breakfast is excellent, and if the weather is good, you can sit out on the terrace.There is a children's play area with paddling room, and some easy chairs for mum and dad. There is a 'wellness' centre and also a roof garden. The (comp.) shuttle to and from the airport works well - the train station is about 500 m. from the airport terminal, and it costs 2 euro and takes about 45-60 mins. to get to the centre of the city. Thus, if you are out sightseeing all day, and just want to return to a hotel to relax and eat dinner/drink wine, this hotel would suit. But if you want to go out in the city in the evening, look elsewhere. We found it peaceful and relaxing and would not hesitate to use it again.All in all an excellent hotel. 
