<Content>Great for Schoenefeld Airport Transfers Stayed there one night in November after arriving at the airport at night and flying out the next morning, booked on line a few days before, got a good rate. It took me a while to find out how to alert them that we were waiting for the transfer bus but the helpful young ladies in yellow caps at Schoenefeld airport pointed out their dedicated 'phone behind the information desk. They spoke English on the 'phone and said the bus was already on its way. It runs every 30 minutes from the Hotel so I'm not sure if they would make a special trip to get you if you had just missed one. As someone else has pointed out it is close to and fantastically convenient for the airport but not so good for Berlin City. We were going to do an early morning dash into Berlin before coming back for the flight but the Airport Express trains tend to run just before the hour and half-hour and their shuttle is on the hour and half hour. As the crow flies its a walkable distance to the station but there might be the railway line in the way, as it was dark I couldn't quite work out if this is possible and safe. The Hotel was very clean, modern and the staff spoke English. They had our on-line booking but offered us an upgrade that we declined; the economy room we had booked was just what we needed for the overnight stay. We had a drink in the bar but didn't use any other facilities or eat there. The transfer back to the airport was fine. 
