<Content>great place/so-so location for tourists I stayed here for 2 nights in August. I was supposed to stay for 5 nights but I changed hotels after 2 days. It is a very nice hotel but it was too far from the city center. The room I had was large and very clean. The bathroom was big and also very clean. The air conditioning was individually controlled so I was very happy with that. The room service menu was not too expensive and the food was actually very good. The staff was friendly and very helpful. They get a lot of airline employees staying there and they all seemed to know eachother or they were trying to out-do eachother's expertise in being frendly. The only reason I checked out early was because it took an hour to get to Alexanderplatz. That includes waiting for the free shuttle to the train station and then waiting for the train and then taking the train. And that was taking the airport express train. It sometimes took more than an hour depending on the waiting. So, if you want to rest before going out to dinner after a day of sight seeing you end up traveling more than 4 hours in a day. It was too much after 2 days so I checked out. It is great if you want to be near the airport. It is not good if you want to tour Berlin for more than a day. 
